As with ANY contractor, you (as the contractee) cannot dictate
their working habits, methods or place of work.  So with any 
consultant you might have the "how many hours?" problem.

Generally, a professional will give you an itemized bill showing
exactly what was done and when.

Some HTML consultants get paid by the hour (with typical rates being
US$50 - US$70), but some will fix-bid, giving you a specific price
for a specific job.  In such cases, be sure you have exact specifications,
or that you allow for a specificiation phase, after which deliverables
can be scheduled.  

On longer projects, it would be typical for a fixed-bid contract to
include a partial up-front payment, and interim payments when milestone
deliverables are completed, with a final payment at the end.

Hope this helps.

