  This is true.  I do freelance HTML work.  I don't charge hourly fees
for one simple reason: logically, after a year or two of experience
doing it, I'll be better and much faster.  So the same job I'm doing
in 2 hours now might take me 1/2 hour in a year...  So should my
prices go DOWN as I get better?
  Also, I don't want to worry that I will (a) hurry a job in order to
fit into an estimate, or (b) avoid hurrying in order to increase the
price.

  I charge by the page, myself, which is rich with problems of its
own, and another story.  The important thing here is that regardless
of whether it's hourly or by the page or what, an estimate is made
beforehand and followed.  If you agree to an hourly fee without an
estimate, you might as well just say "charge me whatever you feel like."
