Actually, they wouldn't. As you got better and better, you would raise 
your prices to reflect your talents. As a beginner, you might charge 
$15/hr, which would be $30 for the 2 hour job you mentioned. When you're 
good enough to do it four times faster, you could charge $60/hr, and the 
1/2 hour job would also net you $30. You wouldn't lose money, because 
you'd be able to do 4 times as much work in the same time, so you'd 
quadruple your income.

