fixed price contracts are a valid way to purchase web pages only if
you know exactly what you want.  When I deal with a customer that
doesn't know what they want, I spend many hours trying to draw out
requirements and get them to think about the problem.  

Every time I've just done what the customer asked for at first, I've
ended up with an angry customer because what they asked for wasn't
what they wanted.

when doing any graphical (or any) design, the customer must always be
involved and sign off on any accepted designs.  That way you protect
yourself someone from folks that change their minds frequently.

