Check out "The Designer's Commonsense Business Book" by 
Barbara Ganim. Graphic designers have had to deal with these 
kinds of issues for years, and Barbara's book is the clearest I've 
read on issues regarding pricing, customer changes, and so on. Also, 
there are many books on how desktop publishers and typesetters 
can/should price their work. I personally find most HTML coding to be 
a (very simplistic) version of entering typsetting codes, and most page 
design to be very similar (in terms of the process followed) to graphic design. 

I think anyone with questions about billing, pricing, quoting, invoicing, and so on
would do well to study the business and billing practices of both graphic designers 
and typesetters/DTPers.

